SENATE BILL No. 123
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
education.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 20-34-3-28 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
2 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
3 1, 2026]: Sec. 28. (a) Each public school, including a charter school,
4 shall present an informational video on water safety each school
5 year to students enrolled in kindergarten through grade 12.
6 (b) The department shall approve an informational video on
7 water safety for use by public schools, including charter schools,
8 under subsection (a) for each group of the following grade levels:
9 (1) Kindergarten through grade 6.
10 (2) Grades 7 and 8.
11 (3) Grades 9 through 12.
12 (c) Each informational video on water safety approved under
13 subsection (b):
14 (1) may be developed by a nonprofit organization or
15 individual with a commitment to water safety and swimming
16 instruction; and
17 (2) shall include instruction on the following topics:
2026 IN 123—LS 6440/DI 152

2
1 (A) The flip, float, and follow method for water safety.
2 (B) Awareness of water conditions.
3 (C) Safe behaviors in and around the water.
4 (D) The importance of:
5 (i) pool barriers and fencing; and
6 (ii) formal swim lessons.
